1. Download the MongoDB .tar.gz tarball
2. Extract the files from the downloaded archive using command
     tar -zxvf mongodb-linux-*-4.0.2.tgz
3. The MongoDB binaries are in the bin/ directory of the tarball.
4. Copy these binaries into a directory listed in your PATH variable such as /usr/local/bin, 
5. using CD command first travel to bin/ directory and then use command
   cp -r * /usr/local/bin
6. create directory on home as "data/db".
7. run your server as
   mongod --dbpath "data/db" --port 27017 --logpath data/db/1.log --fork
8. run client as
   mongo --port 27017
9. Now your ready to work with mongodb.

